Chapter 1: The 0.1% Threshold
The heavy scent of ozone and old parchment always filled the Grand Hall of Aethelgard Academy. High above, the enchanted ceiling mimicked a stormy sky, a constant reminder of the "Fractures" that bled into their world.
Cian kept his head down, scribbling notes on Rune-Scribe Theory while the rest of the class whispered. He wasn't like the others. In a school built for the scions of Great Houses—the "Awakened" who could move mountains with a flick of a wrist—Cian was an anomaly.
He was a "Dormant."
A holographic interface, visible only to him, flickered in his peripheral vision. It was a taunt he’d lived with since he was twelve.
> [System Status: RESTRICTED]
> User: Cian Thorne
> Mana Capacity: 0.01% (Locked)
> Condition: The Seal of the First King
> Progress to Unlocking: 99.9%
> 
So close, he thought, his grip tightening on his pen. Always at 99.9%.
"Still trying to wish that Mana into existence, Thorne?"
The voice belonged to Lyra Valerius. She was the heiress to the Solar Crest, and her presence alone seemed to brighten the dim hall. She leaned against the desk next to his, her eyes—gold and swirling with latent fire—scanning his notebook.
"The midterm is a live-fire simulation in the Obsidian Spire," Lyra said softly, her voice dropping the arrogant edge she used for the public. "If your System doesn't activate by tomorrow, the Council will revoke your scholarship. You’ll be sent to the Outer Rim, Cian."
Cian looked up, meeting her gaze. There was a history there—years of shared childhood before her powers had flared and his had stayed buried. "I'm not leaving, Lyra. I’ve put in the work."
"Work doesn't kill Shadow-Stalkers," she countered, her hand briefly brushing his as she set a small, glowing crystal on his desk. "Take this. It’s a Mana Battery. If the examiners see you can at least light a sigil, they might let you stay."
Cian looked at the crystal. It was an expensive gift, a gesture of pity he hated, but a lifeline he couldn't ignore.
Before he could respond, the stormy ceiling of the hall didn't just mimic a tempest—it cracked.
A sound like tearing silk echoed through the room. The air grew frigid, and a jagged, pitch-black fissure opened directly above the Professor's desk. It wasn't a controlled training exercise.
It was a Gate Rupture.
A notification chime rang in Cian’s head, louder than any alarm.
> [CRITICAL ALERT]
> Condition Met: Proximity to High-Density Void Energy.
> Final 0.1% Acquired.
> The Seal of the First King... BROKEN.
> 
A wave of heat exploded from Cian’s chest, shattering the Mana Battery Lyra had given him. He felt his veins burn with a cold, dark power that felt nothing like the "Light" the Academy taught.
From the black fissure, a skeletal hand draped in purple flames emerged. The students screamed, diving for cover, but Cian stood his ground. His vision was swarmed with new text.
> [Class Selection Available]
>  * Void Monarch (Unique-Rank)
>  * Soul Devourer (Cursed-Rank)
>  * Eclipse Knight (Legendary-Rank)
> 
"Cian, get back!" Lyra shouted, her hands igniting with golden flames as she stepped in front of him.
But Cian didn't move back. He stepped forward, reaching into the air as if grasping a hilt that wasn't there yet.
"My turn, Lyra," he whispered.
